<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kyle McFadzean scored a late winner to give Coventry their first victory since their promotion back to the Championship.</p>

<p>Coventry took the lead just after half-time as goals by Matt Godden and Callum O'Hare cancelled out Lyndon Dykes' opener from the penalty spot.</p>

<p>Yoann Barbet thought he salvaged a point in the 75th minute for Queens Park Rangers, but McFadzean's late winner meant the Sky Blues took all three points. </p>

<p>More to follow... </p>

<p>Kyle McFadzean's 84th minute winner handed Coventry their first win of the new season</p>

<p>Lyndon Dykes (left) opened the scoring for the visitors after he converted a first-half penalty</p>

<p>Queens Park Rangers' lead lasted just three minutes after Matt Godden headed home</p>

<p>Callum O'Hare then put the Sky Blues ahead just five minutes into the second-half of the game</p>

<p>Yoann Barbet scored with 15 minutes to go giving the visitors a chance of getting an away win</p>
